🏛️ Pokémon Card Museum-Bank (PCM)

Core idea:
A vaulted museum where assets are both displayed and liquid.

Think:

The Louvre × a Swiss bank × a stock exchange — for Pokémon cards

⸻

1. 🧱 Core Structure (Simple Model)

A. Vault Layer (The Bank)
	•	Cards are:
	•	Authenticated (PSA, Beckett, etc.)
	•	Stored in high-security vaults
	•	Ownership is digitally recorded
	•	Physical movement = minimized (huge)

👉 This solves:
	•	Theft risk
	•	Shipping damage
	•	Fraud

⸻

B. Display Layer (The Museum)
	•	Cards are curated into exhibits
	•	Example rooms:
	•	“1st Edition Hall”
	•	“Charizard Gallery”
	•	“Error Cards Wing”
	•	“Modern Grails”

Visitors:
	•	Walk through like a museum
	•	Scan cards → see:
	•	Owner
	•	Price history
	•	Last sale
	•	Offers

👉 This taps into status + beauty + story

⸻

C. Ownership Layer (The Exchange)

Here’s where it gets powerful:
	•	You don’t move the card
	•	You move ownership rights

Like:
	•	Stocks
	•	Art funds
	•	Real estate shares

Options:
	1.	Full ownership transfer
	2.	Fractional ownership
	3.	Auction inside the museum system

⸻

